-- Lukoil Completes 52 Million-Euro Bulgarian Wind Farm Purchase
-- B y   E l i z a b e t h   K o n s t a n t i n o v a
-- 2012-06-29T07:47:28Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-29/lukoil-completes-52-million-euro-bulgarian-wind-farm-purchase.html
LUKERG  Renew, a joint venture
between  Italy ’s  ERG SpA (ERG)  and Russia’s OAO Lukoil, completed a 52
million-euro ($65.4 million) acquisition of a 40-megawatt wind
farm near the city of Dobrich in northern Bulgaria, the Moscow-
based company said in an e-mail today.  LUKERG Renew controls some 10 percent of the Bulgarian
wind market after the buying the wind park, which was built in
2009, it said. Lukoil also owns Bulgaria’s biggest refinery
Lukoil Neftochim Burgas.  Bulgaria aims to meet its European Union target of raising
the share of renewable energy in final consumption to 16 percent
in 2020 from 12 percent now. The target share of electricity
produced by wind and solar parks, hydro- and geothermal  power
plants  is 21 percent by 2020 from 16 percent now, according to
the Energy and Economy Ministry.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Elizabeth Konstantinova at 
 ekonstantino@bloomberg.net  